'''''Who's Afraid of Conceptual Art''''' is a 2009 book by [[Elisabeth Schellekens]] and [[Peter Goldie]], in which the authors provide a philosophical introduction to [[conceptual art]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Strayer |first1=Jeffrey |title=Review: Peter Goldie and Elisabeth Schellekens Who’s Afraid of Conceptual Art? |journal=Philosophy in Review |date=2010 |issue=6 |pages=400-403 |url=https://journals.uvic.ca/index.php/pir/article/download/5370/1877 |accessdate=23 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Review: Peter Goldie and Elisabeth Schellekens. Who’s Afraid of Conceptual Art? London, New York: Routledge |journal=Estetika: The Central European Journal of Aesthetics |date=2010 |volume=XLVII/III |pages=112-120 |url=http://aesthetics.ff.cuni.cz/file_download/25 |accessdate=23 November 2018}}</ref> == References == {{reflist}}
